Rating: 3
This turned out well after a few tweaks to the recipe. Having read others' complaints about it turning out dry, I baked it with the foil tightly on at 375 for 45 mins (as per the box instructions for the no-bake lasagna) and then uncovered for 10 mins, which a perfectly cooked lasagna. Also, I added garlic paste to the pea mixture. For the artichoke filling, instead of using cream, I mixed it with leftover home-made lemon garlic bechamel sauce and some chopped sun-dried tomatoes, adding to the layers of flavors. All in all, a great vegetarian main!

