I made this for Mother's Day and it was a hit. Here's what I changed: I used regular noodles and boiled them before I arranged the dish, like a traditional lasagna. I used part-skim ricotta and part-skim mozzarella. I used 2% milk instead of whipping cream. And I didn't brush the pan with oil before I put anything in it. I tried to lower the fat for health concerns. Next time I would brush the pan with oil and I might add a bit whole milk ricotta. It did feel a bit dry. The dish was amazing and also beautiful--although the vegetables were frozen, it felt and tasted very spring-y. It was a perfect dish for this time of year and was quite delicious. However, it is best eaten the day you make it. It really didn't match up in later days, so be sure to cook for a crowd or invite good eaters!

